what's your favorite lime recipe i have four regular limes and i can't decide what to do with them i don't drink tequila stir fry lime and coconut chicken ingredients free range chicken beasts cut into bite sized pieces lime zest and juice tbsp olive oil ml fl oz low fat coconut milk tbsp thai fish sauce nam pla tbsp roughly chopped fresh coriander leaves spring onions finely sliced g oz brown rice method place the chicken pieces lime zest and juice into a large bowl and toss through to coat thoroughly heat the olive oil in a large deep frying pan or wok over a high heat add the chicken pieces and stir fry for minutes until golden brown all over add coconut milk fish sauce two tablespoons of the coriander and half of the spring onions and stir fry for a further minutes on a lower heat until the chicken is cooked through meanwhile boil the rice in a large saucepan according to packet instructions or until the grains are tender then drain to serve share the rice out evenly between three or four dishes and spoon over portions of the lime and coconut chicken sprinkle with remaining coriander and the remaining spring onions and serve Tofu Curry Cuisine of Singapore Cuisine of Thailand Bengali cuisine Cantonese cuisine French fries Cuisine of Laos Cuisine of Malaysia Japanese cuisine Cajun cuisine Peruvian cuisine Cuisine of Brazil Laksa Jewish cuisine Cuisine of Cambodia Korean cuisine Cuisine of Denmark Coffee Breakfast Kelantan Soul food Barbecue Salad Hamburger Ramen Chicken soup Stir frying Risotto Idli Recipe Pizza Dim sum Russian cuisine Hot dog Soup Mayonnaise Satay German cuisine French cuisine McDonald's Paella Coconut milk Pancake Cuisine of Greece D__ner kebab Porridge Fried rice Ice cream Veganism Deep frying Gumbo Rice Gazpacho Cha chaan teng MRE Canadian Chinese cuisine Kebab Rice pudding Bacon Sauce Chinese cuisine Cookware and bakeware Potato pancakes Wok Plantain Sushi Milk Ketchup Domesticated turkey In-N-Out Burger Rum Cooking Martini cocktail American